<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08238</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO AMEND REPUBLIC ACT 9994 OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE EXPANDED SENIOR CITIZENS ACT OF 2010 AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to give certain classes of senior citizens graduated discount which will amend specifically Sec. 4 of R.A.9994 on the grant of 20% discount.

Provides for:  TWENTY PERCENT (20%) discount for those who are 60 – 70 years old;
THIRTY PERCENT (30%) discount for those who are 70 – 80 years old;  
FORTY PERCENT  (40%) discount for those who are 80 – 90 years old; and
FIFTY PERCENT (50%) discount for those who are 90 years old or over.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C., MACEDA, EDWARD VERA PEREZ, MARTINEZ, ERIC M., SANDOVAL, FEDERICO &quot;RICKY&quot; II S., MALAPITAN, DALE &quot;ALONG&quot; R., OLIVAREZ, ERIC L., CALIXTO-RUBIANO, EMI G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-12</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-10-08)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON SENIOR CITIZENS ON 2018-09-18</td></tr></table>